text: Turnir (Russian: Турнир, meaning Tournament) is a home video game console. It was released in 1978 only in the Soviet Union. It was sold for 150 Russian ruble in 1978 and 96 Russian ruble in the end of the 1990s. == Games == * теннис () * сквош () * хоккей () * тренировка () == References == Category:Video game consoles Category:Soviet Union
